nv_title_skip_dotted()

Description
    int nv_title_skip_dotted(string $matches)
    Skips words containing dots.  E.g.: del.icio.us

Parameters
    matches
    String value on which to execute a callback function.

Return Values
    Returns a string value; either the original or a modified copy.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
        for ($i = 0; $i < count($words); $i++) {
        // Skip words with dots in them like del.icio.us
        $words[$i] = preg_replace_callback('/\b([[:alpha:]][[:lower:].\'â€™(&\#8217;)]*)\b/x', 'nv_title_skip_dotted', $words[$i]);
	}
	...
    ?>

See Also
    str2TitleCase()
